        <body >
            <div style="font-size: 17px;">
               
                <h2 style="text-align:center;">AGREEMENT OF ASSIGNMENT</h2><br/>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                     THIS AGREEMENT OF ASSIGNMENT is made and executed on this date <apex:outputText value="{0, DATE, dd'-'MM'-'yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!today()}" /></apex:outputText> at Bangalore.</p>
                <p>
                    BETWEEN;
                </p>
                <p style="font-size:17px;">
                     {!Booking__c.First_Applicant_Name__c}, W/o/S/o/C/o. {!Booking__c.W_o_S_o_C_o__c}, Aged about {!Booking__c.Age__c} years,<br/>
                    PAN No: {!Booking__c.PAN_Number__c}, Aadhar No. {!Booking__c.Aadhar_Number__c}.<br/><br/>
                    <apex:repeat value="{!Booking__c.Co_Applicants__r}" var="p">
                         {!p.Name}, W/o/S/o/C/o. {!p.W_o_S_o_C_o__c}, Aged about {!p.Age__c} years,<br/>
                        PAN No: {!p.PAN_Number__c}, Aadhar No. {!p.Aadhar_Number__c}.<br/><br/>
                    </apex:repeat>
                    Both are residing at {!Booking__c.Address__c}
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    Hereinafter referred to as the <b>ASSIGNOR/S</b> (which expression shall mean and include their respective heirs, legal representatives, executors, 
                    administrators and assigns etc) OF THE <b>FIRST PART:</b>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <b>In Favour of</b> 
                </p>
                <p style="font-size:17px;">
                     {!Booking__c.First_Applicant_Name__c}, W/o/S/o/C/o. {!Booking__c.W_o_S_o_C_o__c}, Aged about {!Booking__c.Age__c} years,<br/>
                    PAN No: {!Booking__c.PAN_Number__c}, Aadhar No. {!Booking__c.Aadhar_Number__c}.<br/><br/>
                    <apex:repeat value="{!Booking__c.Co_Applicants__r}" var="p">
                         {!p.Name}, W/o/S/o/C/o. {!p.W_o_S_o_C_o__c}, Aged about {!p.Age__c} years,<br/>
                        PAN No: {!p.PAN_Number__c}, Aadhar No. {!p.Aadhar_Number__c}.<br/><br/>
                    </apex:repeat>
                    Both are residing at {!Booking__c.Address__c}
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    Hereinafter referred to as the <b>ASSIGNEE/S </b>(which expression shall mean and include their heirs, legal representatives, executors,
                    administrators and assigns etc) OF THE<b>SECOND PART:</b> 
                </p>
                <p>
                    And:
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    <b>M/s. SOWPARNIKA PROJECTS AND INFRASTRUCTURE PRIVATE LIMITED,</b> CIN No. U45201KA2007PTC043166 a company incorporated 
                    under the provisions of the Companies Act, 1956, having its registered office at No.750, ‘C’ Block, 1st Main Road,
                    AECS Layout, Kundalahalli, Bangalore-560037 (PAN– AAKCS9641L). represented by its authorized signatory<b> MR. Purushotham C.
                    Reddy, GM Finance,</b> Authorized vide board resolution dated 30.09.2019
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    Hereinafter referred to as the <b>CONSENTING WITNESS/BUILDER</b> (which expression shall mean and include its, representatives, 
                    executors, administrators, Successors in interest and assigns etc) OF <b>THE THIRD PART:</b>
                </p>
                <div style="page-break-after:always;"></div>
                <p>
                    <b>WITNESSETH:</b>
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    WHEREAS the Assignor/s above named being desirous of owning an Apartment in the project known as<b> “SOWPARNIKA PRANATHI” </b>
                    promoted by M/s Sowparnika Projects and Infrastructure Pvt. Ltd., a Private Limited Company (hereinafter referred to as the
                    BUILDER) joined the scheme of ownership of residential apartments in the said project propounded by the said Builder on the
                    residentially, converted land bearing Re-Survey No.28/17A (Old Survey No.28/17), measuring 1 Acre 34 Guntas
                    (including 01 gunta of Kharab Land), situated at Kumbalagodu Village, Kengeri Hobli, Bangalore South Taluk, which is
                    more-fully and particularly described in the schedule hereunder written and hereinafter referred to as<b> (“Said Land”)</b> having,
                    purchased the same by a  sale Agreement dated 19.03.2018 registered as documents No 265/2018-19 in  the office of the Senior 
                    Sub-Registrar Kengeri Bangalore South Taluk.  which is more fully described in the Schedule A hereunder and hereinafter
                    referred to as the Schedule A Property.
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    The proportionate undivided interest in the Schedule A Property agreed to be purchased by the Assignor/s in terms of the
                    Agreement to sell dated <apex:outputText value="{0, DATE, dd'-'MM'-'yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Sale_Agreement_Date__c}" /></apex:outputText> more fully described in the Schedule B hereunder and hereinafter referred to as the 
                    Schedule A Property.
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    WHEREAS in terms of the scheme propounded by the Builder, the Assignor/s by virtue of agreeing to purchase the Schedule ‘A’
                    Property in terms of the said<b> Agreement to Sell dated<apex:outputText value="{0, DATE, dd'-'MM'-'yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Sale_Agreement_Date__c}" /></apex:outputText> and agreed to get constructed an Apartment bearing No. {!Booking__c.Unit_NumberFor__c} in the {!Booking__c.Floor__c} Floor, in the project known as “SOWPARNIKA PRANATHI”,</b> more fully described in the Schedule
                    ‘A’ hereunder, through the Builder above named.
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                   <b> WHEREAS in terms of the Sale Agreement dated <apex:outputText value="{0, DATE, dd'-'MM'-'yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Sale_Agreement_Date__c}" /></apex:outputText>, the Builder had agreed to construct the Schedule ‘A’ Apartment for
                       total cost of Rs.{!totalCostInString}/- excluding Tax.</b>
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    WHEREAS the Assignor/s has obtained a housing <b>loan from {!Booking__c.Bank_Name__c} and the bank has disbursed the amount of Rs. <apex:outputText value="{0,number}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Sanctioned_Amount__c}" /></apex:outputText>/- </b>to the builder.  Now Assignors have no longer interested in owning the Schedule ‘A’ Apartment and hence
                    are desirous of disposing off their right, title and interest in the Schedule ‘A’  Properties acquired in terms of the Sale Agreement 
                    <b>dated <apex:outputText value="{0, DATE, dd'-'MM'-'yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Sale_Agreement_Date__c}" /></apex:outputText>.</b>
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    WHEREAS the Assignee/s above named being desirous of owning an apartment has agreed to purchase the Schedule ‘A’ Property for
                    total consideration of Rs.{!totalCostInString}/- excluding tax from the builder.  Hence the
                    Assignor/s and the Assignee/s have entered into this Assignment Agreement in terms of which the Assignor/s above named have
                    assigned all their right, title and interest acquired by them under the Sale Agreement dated <apex:outputText value="{0, DATE, dd'-'MM'-'yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Sale_Agreement_Date__c}" /></apex:outputText> in favour
                    of the Assignee/s. 
                </p>
                <div style="page-break-after:always;"></div>
                                    <h2 style="text-align:center;">NOW THIS AGREEMENT OF ASSIGNMENT WITNESSETH AS FOLLOWS:</h2><br/>
                 <p style="text-align:justify;">
                     In Pursuance of the above and in consideration the Assignee has agreed to pay    Rs.-------------------/- (Rupees ------------------------ Only) 
                     to Assignor and to the builder/ consenting witnesses herein in the following  manner: -
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    a)	Rs. __________/- (Rupees ___________ Only) shall pay to __________________Bank to close the Assignor housing loan.  
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    b)	Rs. ________/- (Rupees _________ Only) shall pay to Assignor
                </p >
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    c)	The balance consideration of Rs._______/- (Rupees ________ Only) shall pay to builder/ consenting witness.
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    d)	Assignee has paid Rs. ________/-(Rupees _______ Only) to the builder as advance consideration, 
                    Balance of Rs.___________/- (Rupees _________ Only) shall be paid to the builder.
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    The Assignor/s hereby assign, transfer and make over unto the Assignee/s all his/her/their right, title and interest in the
                    Sale Agreement dated ___________ in favour of the Assignee/s and the Assignee/s hereby accepts the assignment. 
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    1.	The Assignor/s has agreed to pay to the builder the Assignment fee of Rs. <apex:outputText value="{0,number}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Assignment_Fee__c}" /></apex:outputText>/- per Sq.ft of Rs. <apex:outputText value="{0,number}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Assignment_Amount__c}" /></apex:outputText>/-.
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    2.	The Assignor/s hereby confirm and declare that they have not violated any terms and conditions of the Sale Agreement
                    dated <apex:outputText value="{0, DATE, dd'-'MM'-'yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Sale_Agreement_Date__c}" /></apex:outputText> and the said Sale Agreement is valid, subsisting and binding that they have not created any right 
                    or charge in favour of any third parties nor have encumbered their right in favour of any third parties except for housing
                    loan from {!Booking__c.Bank_Name__c} for purchase of the Schedule ‘B’ Properties which the Assignor undertake to clear before execution 
                    of sale deed in favor of Assignee. 
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    3.	In case of any such charge or encumbrance, the Assignee shall be entitled to call upon the Assignor to discharge such charge,
                    encumbrance or right at the cost of the Assignor/s.
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    4.	The Assignee/s hereby assures and covenants that they shall observe and confirm to all terms, conditions, covenants, and obligations etc,
                    detailed in the Sale Agreement dated <apex:outputText value="{0, DATE, dd'-'MM'-'yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Sale_Agreement_Date__c}" /></apex:outputText> and that they are bound by all such terms, conditions, covenants as if the Sale Agreement
                    dated <apex:outputText value="{0, DATE, dd'-'MM'-'yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Sale_Agreement_Date__c}" /></apex:outputText> is entered into and executed by Assignor/s.  
                </p>
                <br/><br/> <br/><br/><br/> <br/>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    5.	The Assignor/s hereby declares and confirms that by virtue of this assignment they have extinguished all their right, title and interest in the
                    Schedule ‘B’ Properties and the Assignee/s is entitled to get the conveyance deed registered in Their name and take possession from the Builder of the
                    Schedule ‘B’ apartment after payment of the Assignment fee as stated above.
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    6.	The Builder has consented to this assignment by the Assignor/s in favour of the Assignee/s and has agreed to hand over the possession of the Schedule ‘B’ 
                    apartment to the Assignee/s and in token thereof the Builder has executed this Agreement as a Consenting Witness.  
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    7.	The Assignor/s shall hand over original Sale Agreement dated <apex:outputText value="{0, DATE, dd'-'MM'-'yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!Booking__c.Sale_Agreement_Date__c}" /></apex:outputText> to the Assignee/s or to the Assignee Banker within 15 days from the date of closing
                    existing housing loan.   
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    8.	The Assignee/s hereby assures and declares the Builder that he will get the Schedule B Property registered in their name or in the name of their heirs, legal representatives,
                    assigns etc. 
                </p>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    9.	The original of this Assignment agreement shall be retained by the Assignee/s and the photo copy shall be retained by the Assignor/s and Builder.   
                </p>
                <h2 style="text-align:center;">SCHEDULE PROPERTY</h2>
                <p style="text-align:justify;">
                    All that piece and parcel of residential converted land bearing No.28/17, Re-Survey No.28/17-A, (Converted vide Official
                    Memorandum No- B.Dis.ALN (S) SR(KT) 136/2004-05 dated 09-05-2005 issued by Special Deputy Commissioner, Bangalore District)
                    having  E-Katha Property No.150200300200220412, situated at Kumbalagodu Village, Kengeri  Hobli, Bangalore South Taluk, measuring
                    an extent of 1 Acres 34 Guntas (1-34) together with all rights, appurtenances whatsoever whether underneath or above the surface
                    and bounded on:
                </p>
                <p>
                    East by	: Eeranarasappa, Channamma Garden (Sy No.29) 
                </p>
                <p>
                    West by	: Road,
                </p>
                <p>
                    North by	: Narasimhaiah and Dasappa’s Land (Sy No.28)
                </p>
                <p>
                    South by	: Private Property (Sy No.32)
                </p>
